Project Specifications:

Hardware: 
- Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W
- 128x64 px OLED display
    -Connections: SPI 
        VCC             ->    5V (Pin 2)
        GND             ->    Ground (Pin 6)
        DIN (MOSI)      ->    GPIO 10 (MOSI) (Pin 19)
        CLK (SCLK)      ->    GPIO 11 (SCLK) (Pin 23)
        CS              ->    GPIO 8 (CE0) (Pin 24)
        DC              ->    GPIO 24 (Pin 18)
        RST             ->    GPIO 25 (Pin 22)
    -Orientation: Landscape


API's to include: each one is configurable to be displayed or not through a settings file
Weather: https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast?latitude=52.52&longitude=13.41&daily=temperature_2m_max,temperature_2m_min,sunset,sunrise&hourly=precipitation_probability&current=temperature_2m&timezone=America%2FChicago&wind_speed_unit=mph&temperature_unit=fahrenheit&precipitation_unit=inch


Also include: current date and time - always

EXAMPLE SETUP:
